**What was tested.** Four new pairwise-unmixing datasets
(`HCR_<sid>_pairwise-unmixing_2026-04-29_*`) provide per-cell unmixed
spot counts with column `R{1,2}-488-GFP` (R1 for 782149/788406, R2 for
755252/767022) inside `pairwise_unmixing/all_cells_unmixed/unmixed_all_cells.csv`.
The `cell_id` matches HCR `hcr_id` (level-2 centroid id space). Coverage
is partial (47–66 % of total HCR cells per subject) — the unmixed CSV
drops cells filtered by unmixing QC.

Two feature variants were threshold-fit with the 07c pipeline
(`fit_gmm_sweep` K∈[2,6], BIC-selected, intersection of top-two
components) and gated by `gt_density_gate` (per-bin CV of
ρ_GFP+/ρ_CZ inside GT-Procrustes-mapped overlap, 25-µm bins, 0.20
bar from 07c):

|              | 755252 | 767022 | 782149 | 788406 |
|--------------|-------:|-------:|-------:|-------:|
| baseline (density) CV | n/a* | n/a* | **0.332** | **0.226** |
| unmixed count CV      | 0.394 | 0.342 | 0.544 | 0.370 |
| unmixed count/vol CV  | n/a† | n/a† | 0.561 | 0.456 |
| baseline n_strict / total | n/a | n/a | 3450/29 556 (11.7 %) | 10 729/90 814 (11.8 %) |
| unmixed n_strict / total  | 2216/39 895 | 2388/40 701 | 2673/25 721 | 7572/81 426 |
| K* baseline | n/a | n/a | 4 | 6 |
